{
  "text": "With some probability, the quantizer will still be in the perfect-zoom phase: z+1 = z + 1. In case perfect-zoom is lost, there is a uniform bound on when the zoom is expected to be recovered. It follows that, conditioned on increment in the error, until the next stopping time, the process will increase exponentially and hence We now show that, there exist > 0, jGj < 1 such that E log 1 2 j1 ; h log 1 2 0 + G1 fj1 jF g : [CITATION_1] Now, it follows that: E log 1 2 j1 ; h (1 0 P e (1 )) 2 log jaj jaj + 0 + log 1 2 + P e (1 )E [2( z+1 0 z ) log (jaj + ) + 2 log (1 )] :",
